<br>
KEI has hurt the groupablity of lower level enchanters. People don't need the lower level mana regeneration when they have KEI, and have come to realize that the general style of play that is popular in experience groups doesn't require crowd control. In any event, it seems that KEI for all is on the way out, and this would help ease the pain a bit.<br>
<br>
KEI is not the answer to super twinked melees, there are plenty of super melee buffs that will be gone also. It is unfortunate that there is a disparity in non level restricted items between casters and melee, but KEI was never intended to make up the difference. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lunaltoadsnatcher>Lunal Toadsnatcher</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 1443<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/19/03 4:55:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26593.topic&index=23>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A Caster Balancing idea -- for enchanters!</span><hr size=1> Familiars affecting an entire group..hmmm I like it!<br>
