e: A Caster Balancing idea -- for enchanters!</span><hr size=1> The biggest problem with KEI is not the amount of mana regen, its the duration.  With AA and focus items you can get a four hour KEI.  If they made two brand new buffs: a four hour duration 9 mana/tic buff, and a 28 minute lasting 14 mana/tic buff, which would you buy in the nexus?<br>
<br>
<br>
The former would be more imbalancing in terms of how much a level 20 could kill in 28 minutes, but the latter would do more to screw low level enchanters out of groups.<br>
<br>
<br>
Back on topic, I like the idea, Whiz.  One benefit of your plan you didn't mention is it would take out some of the redundancy of some of the clarity line.<br>
<br>
Currently with group c1 being level 52 and c2 being level 54, there are only two levels to enjoy the convenience of group c1.  Group c2 at 59 quickly followed up with kei at 60 means only one level of usefulness of group c2.  Tranquilty at 63 is a friggin joke with VoQ just two levels away. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=necridious>Necridious</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 300<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/20/03 12:01:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26593.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://personal.atl.bellsouth.net/atl/d/a/dastorys/Pictures/Nec-60x60.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A Caster Balancing idea -- for enchanters!</span><hr size=1> KEI is not overbalanced.  It returned balance to what it should have been without it.  At times, I found it a bit weak.  When I play a game, I'm not looking to have time to clean house, do dishes, finish Homework, read a book, watch TV ect, ect while I'm playing.  I'm looking to play a game.<br>
<br>
<br>
The real problem is that mana regen is too slow.  It makes the game boring as hell to have to wait so long on mana.<br>
<br>
Perhaps if there were potions that could be bought that work similar to Spirit of the Cheetah, only give huge mana Regen instead of speed.  Get in a fight, you lose the buff.<br>
<br>
Health is not so bad, because you can find a healer and be full health in a matter of seconds, but no one can do the same for mana.  The only people that can--Necromancers-- pay such a high price when they do grant mana, it's a huge hit in efficency, with no wonder the necro community regards the spell line as a sick kind of joke. <p><br>
