<br>
I'll second that!  They put in the focus stuff and oh so intelligently level capped all of it to...balance casters against melees wearing level 50+ level drops??  Hello!  Anybody home, SOE?<br>
<br>
If they actually do put a minimum level cap on KEI I'll say it's a good move because it will mean they'll have to balance damage casters for real this time.I never liked KEI being used as some kind of cure-all bandaid for caster balance issues.  You don't balance one class by overpowering another.<br>
<br>
I don't think KEI hurt low level enchanters in groups though.  Melees love speed probably more than casters love KEI and enchanters have the best haste spells.  Plus the groups my ench was in started chainpulling in bulk whenever I joined so crowd control is still an effective grouping tool.  As long as the pullers were hopped up on enough caffiene to do it.<br>
